HEADWORD: bully pulpit
<hw>bul"ly pul"pit</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An
exceptionally advantageous position from which to extol one's ideas; --
applied especially to the presidency of the United States, which was
described thus by President Theodore Roosevelt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

